title.narrative: 4.3 Parents/caregivers and adolescents are better informed to prevent and respond to violence and harmful practices.

description.narrative: In 2021, an additional 21,343 parents/caregivers and children were reached to help prevent and raise awareness on reporting instances of violence and harmful practices with 28,032 individuals reached cumulatively over two years, which is on-track for the CPD target of 61,200 people. UNICEF supported the government so that an increased number of people are better informed to respond to violence and harmful practices. Significant progress was made in evidence-generation initiatives and foundational work for social norms programming, including a survey on social and behavioral drivers of child marriage, launching a positive parenting education programme pilot, and school-related GBV research. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
